{{expand Italian|Teatro Adriano|date=September 2015}}
[[File:Prati - teatro Adriano 1040957.JPG|290px|thumbnail|Teatro Adriano]]
The '''Teatro Adriano''' (i.e. "Adriano Theater"), also known as  '''Politeama Adriano''' and '''Cinema Adriano''', is a cinema and former theatre located in Piazza Cavour, [[Rome]], [[Italy]]. 

It was built by Pio Gallas and Romeo Bisini on a project by architect Luigi Rolland (the father of [[Luigi Moretti]]) and inaugurated on 1 June 1898 with a representation of the [[Amilcare Ponchielli]]'s opera [[La Gioconda (opera)|La Gioconda]] conducted by [[Edoardo Mascheroni]].<ref>Silvana Matarazzo. ''Teatri a Roma tra storia e contemporaneità''. Napoli: Edizioni Intra Moenia, 2004. {{ISBN|8874210418}}.</ref>

